<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#242422><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bblacktower89939.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ozric>ozric</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Local user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#939393>5/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#939393>4:09:33 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fblacktower89939publicforum.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=6><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: But That's Just It</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I realize this is information for an entirely different thread, however, I just thought I'd offer this tidbit of information in light of Adita's comparison, hehe.  Hell levels, although the psychological equivalent of a catastrophic earthquake, are not a bug either.  <br>
<br>
The number of experience points needed for advancement is recalculated every five levels.  This is done by using a perceived step basis, but in actuality is a mathmatical curve.  The rate of this curve is changed every five levels, creating what looks to be a normal curve with an increasingly steep grade toward the higher levels.  However, due to the nature of recalculating a curve after the grade increase without wiping out previous experience points gained, the amount of experience you gained is actually BELOW the starting point of the NEW curve.  So in actuality, during the &quot;hell level&quot; you are simply &quot;catching up&quot; to the new curve.  Notice how quickly exp bar movement is gained in 46 compared to 45?  Now compare 46 to 36.  36 moved faster.  Because the curve was less steep.  Now 47, 48, and 49 will be increasingly more difficult than was 46, as it should be.  Then 50 will recalculate the curve once again, and you will have your existing exp points in a curve that would ordinarily require FAR more exp points to BE 50.  So you will have to &quot;catch up&quot;.  That's the &quot;hell level&quot; phenomenon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So why not wipe previous exp, and start over with enough exp to begin the new curve?  Death.  If you die, you lose your level.  Suddenly, you are back to somewhere in the old exp level, but those exp points are now gone... so you're level 1 again.  Oops.  If they made it impossible to lose a level every 5 levels to retain the &quot;new&quot; exp, then people would abuse this to &quot;explore&quot; or rather exploit new areas without fear of loss.  Personally, I think they should have just spread out the levels of each &quot;hell level&quot; more evenly in terms of the cute little graphic bar, thus keeping the mathmatical anomaly from being revealed to the user, but it was their choice to allow it to be viewed, and now they have to deal with the bitching, hehe.  But trust me, there is no such thing as a &quot;hell level bug&quot;, it's simply catching up to the exp curve, and yes it does suck if you sit and watch the bar move... or NOT move, hehe.  Eternally 45, Kodi.<br>
<br>
-p.s.- I appreciate the explanation of the tracking mystery, Tesh.  I always thought it was a bug too, and am glad to understand it at last, hehe.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bblacktower89939.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=adita>Adita</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Local user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#939393>5/31/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#939393>10:55:50 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fblacktower89939publicforum.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=7><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: But That's Just It</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">You have to explain me what you think what a bug is then ...<br>
